================================================================================

This project includes or depends on the following third-party software:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

GBDK-2020
https://github.com/gbdk-2020/gbdk-2020
License: Various (GPL for compiler, custom licenses for libraries)
Used for: Game Boy ROM compilation

The GBDK toolchain is used at build time to compile generated C code into
Game Boy ROMs. GBDK-2020 is not distributed with gbkt; users must install
it separately.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

EmulatorJS
https://emulatorjs.org/
https://github.com/EmulatorJS/EmulatorJS
License: GPL-3.0
Used for: Web export feature (browser-based Game Boy emulation)

EmulatorJS is loaded from CDN in the web export feature. It is not bundled
with gbkt. The web export generates HTML that references EmulatorJS remotely.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

mGBA
https://mgba.io/
https://github.com/mgba-emu/mgba
License: MPL-2.0
Used for: Development emulation, live reload, and debugging

mGBA is the recommended emulator for development. It is not distributed
with gbkt; users must install it separately. The gbkt Gradle plugin can
auto-detect and launch mGBA for testing.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

hUGETracker / hUGEDriver
https://github.com/SuperDisk/hUGETracker
License: MIT
Used for: Music playback on Game Boy hardware

hUGEDriver is used for playing .uge music files on Game Boy. The driver
code is linked into compiled ROMs when music features are used.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

IMPORTANT NOTICE FOR GAME DEVELOPERS:

Games created with gbkt are YOUR property. The MPL-2.0 license applies only
to the gbkt framework itself, not to games you create. You may:

- Sell your games commercially
- Keep your game's source code private
- Use any license you choose for your game
- Distribute your ROM files freely

The only requirement is that if you modify the gbkt framework source code
itself, those modifications must be made available under the MPL-2.0.
